Charles H. Esserman: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 12:51 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of TSG Consumer Partners



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Charles H. Esserman  Co-Founder and Chief Executive Officer, TSG Consumer PartnersAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships59--
Background

		Mr. Charles H. Esserman, also known as Chuck, is a Co-Founder and serves as Chief Executive Officer of TSG Consumer Partners. He served as a Managing Director at the firm. Mr. Esserman has over 25 years of private equity investment experience and together with the partners of TSG, built the first and most experienced consumer focused equity fund in the United States. He is a Principal at Palomitas Properties LLC. Prior to that, he worked at Communications Satellite Corporation ... and played a leading role in strategic planning. He was also employed at Bain & Company, Inc. and assisted a wide array of consumer product companies in evaluating acquisitions, implementing cost-reduction and marketing strategies. Additionally, he assisted in founding software companies at the infancy of the personal computer industry. Mr. Esserman worked at Met-Rx. He also serves on the Board of Trustees of The Head-Royce School in Oakland. He has been a Director at Planet Fitness, Inc. since November 2012. He is a Member of the Advisory Council at the Stanford Graduate School of Business and a Member of the Board of Overseers of the Hoover Institution. He is the Board of Trust of Vanderbilt University. He served as a Director of Authentic Specialty Foods, Inc. He received an M.B.A. degree from the Stanford University Graduate School of Business, where Mr. Esserman was an Arjay Miller Scholar and a B.S. degree, with top honors, in Electrical Engineering and Computer Science from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology.Read Full Background




