Private Equity Beat




PE Outlook: TSG Consumer Partners’ Chuck Esserman






By

Laura Kreutzer


Laura Kreutzer
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyLaura Kreutzer
@LauraKreutzer
LAURA .KREUTZER@WSJ.com




                    Dec 30, 2010 8:26 pm  ET
                  


As we head into the final days of 2010, we asked several private equity professionals to share their thoughts about where the industry came from in 2010 and where it may be headed in the year to come.
Today, Charles ‘Chuck’ Esserman, chief executive of TSG Consumer Partners, a New York-based mid market buyout firm focused on consumer product companies, shares his thoughts on the economy, the consumer and the challenges ahead.



